<subSubSection id="C3089AA0FFBA5726FF38971A7E79077F" box="[151,786,1294,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBA5726FF38971A7E79077F" blockId="11.[151,786,1294,1318]" box="[151,786,1294,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF38971A7C75077F" bold="true" box="[151,286,1294,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<typeStatus id="54A97789FFBA5726FF38971A7DA7077F" box="[151,204,1294,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FE85971A7F0A077C" authority="Emerson" authorityName="Emerson" authorityYear="1949" box="[298,609,1294,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Armitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FE85971A7C96077F" box="[298,509,1294,1318]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Armitermes silvestrii</emphasis>
Emerson
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF83B4DAFFBA5726FD2A971A7E65077F" author="Snyder, T. E." box="[645,782,1294,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" pagination="1 - 490" refId="ref9141" refString="Snyder, T. E. (1949) Catalog of termites (Isoptera) of the world. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 112 (3953), 1 - 490." type="journal article" year="1949">Snyder, 1949</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3089AA0FFBA5726FF38974079730782" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBA5726FF38974079730782" blockId="11.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF3897407C730737" bold="true" box="[151,280,1364,1390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FE3397407F240737" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" box="[412,591,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FE3397407F240737" box="[412,591,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Bandeiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed in honor of our late colleague and friend Adelmar Gomes Bandeira, a Brazilian termitologist, one of the first to study the Amazonian termites, and an excellent collector who initiated and contributed significantly to termite collections in Manaus, AM (INPA); Belém, PA (Museu Paraense Emílio Goeldi); and later in João Pessoa, PB (Universidade Federal da 
<collectingRegion id="49D607C9FFBA5726FC1C97D4796C0783" box="[947,1031,1472,1498]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3089AA0FFBA5720FF6897F078F80064" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBA5726FF6897F07C3A07A7" blockId="11.[151,1437,1364,2039]" box="[199,337,1508,1534]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF6897F07C3A07A7" bold="true" box="[199,337,1508,1534]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBA5726FF68941C7CF3047B" blockId="11.[151,1437,1364,2039]" box="[199,408,1544,1571]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF68941C7C78047B" bold="true" box="[199,275,1544,1570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Imago</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBA5726FF6894387CB005D3" blockId="11.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF6894387C76041F" bold="true" box="[199,285,1580,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Soldier</emphasis>
. Head elongate, rectangular or sub-rectangular, narrowing slightly towards front with lateral and posterior margins slightly convex and posterolateral angles broadly rounded as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FBA49444784E0433" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1035,1317,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FBA49444784E0433" box="[1035,1317,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Bandeiratermes silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBA5726FA99944478FF0433" box="[1334,1428,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1261,1285]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,633,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-241@12.[151,1435,633,1237]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 13. Soldier of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571697/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
) or with sides parallel from dorsal view (
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FDF894607E1904D7" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[599,882,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tellustris">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FDF894607E1904D7" box="[599,882,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Bandeiratermes tellustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBA5726FC2F94607EB404D6" box="[896,991,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1112,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 16. Soldier of Bandeiratermes tellustris (Ibitermes tellustris paratype). a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571709/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Fig. 16a</figureCitation>
); head thickest at base of conical nasus, which extends forward almost as far as the extended mandibles; in profile dorsal surface of nasus convex near the base, somewhat humped, and somewhat upwards. Mandibles robust, curved inward, without teeth (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FAB594A97DD704A3" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tellustris">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FAB594A97DD704A3" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Ban. tellustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBA5726FF6594F47C4E04A2" box="[202,293,1760,1787]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1112,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 16. Soldier of Bandeiratermes tellustris (Ibitermes tellustris paratype). a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571709/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Fig. 16a</figureCitation>
) or with small tooth on medial surface about one-third of distance from base to tip, tip of tooth rounded (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FF1195117C300547" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[190,347,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF1195117C300547" box="[190,347,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Ban. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBA5726FEC595107CA10547" box="[362,458,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1261,1285]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,633,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-241@12.[151,1435,633,1237]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 13. Soldier of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571697/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
); antenna with 14 articles; anterior margin of lobe of pronotum strongly convex (
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBA5726FAC795117D9C051B" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FAC795117D9C051B" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Ban. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or less so, median notch present or absent, posterior portion with broadly rounded, non-emarginated hind margin. Head sparsely covered with hairs of moderate length, nasus devoid of hairs on top and sides or with a few short hairs on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBA5721FF6895807ECC0344" blockId="11.[151,1437,1364,2039]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="457" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBA5726FF6895807C4F05F7" bold="true" box="[199,292,1940,1966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Worker</emphasis>
. Head capsule rounded. Postclypeus moderately inflated or more inflated. Antenna with 14 articles. Mandibles (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBA5726FEB495AC7C1D058A" box="[283,374,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="456">Fig. 15f</figureCitation>
), [
<bibRefCitation id="EF83B4DAFFBA5726FE3F95AC7F01058B" author="Constantino, R." box="[400,618,1976,2002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="456" pagination="3 - 9" refId="ref8255" refString="Constantino, R. (1990) Two new species of termites (Insecta, Isoptera) from western Brazilian Amazonia. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, Serie Zoologia, 6 (1), 3 - 9." type="journal article" year="1990">Constantino (1990)</bibRefCitation>
figs 9–10)] with apical tooth (A) larger than marginal, acute angle or right between A and second marginal; LM: M1+2 with first very conspicuous or not as so. RM: second marginal tooth smaller than first, angle between them slightly more opened than a right angle. Molar regions without ridges. Head covered by scattered short to medium sized bristles and some very short hairs, which also occur as on postclypeus, along with a few bristles. Pronotum, mesonotum and metanotum with long bristles on margins and shorter bristles and hairs on surface. Head and pronotum pale yellow and legs lighter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBD5721FF6893327E320038" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBD5721FF6893327C040318" bold="true" box="[199,367,294,321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Digestive tube</emphasis>
. Crop asymmetrical. Cuticular armature of gizzard with 24 visible folds, six of these first-order, six second-order and 12 third-order; ratio between columnar and pulvillar belts approximately equal to one; columns covered with pectinate scale (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FD81937B7FFB03D0" box="[558,656,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1309,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-259@12.[151,1435,1309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 14. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, gizzard; b, enteric valve." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571701/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Fig. 14a</figureCitation>
). Insertion of stomodeal valve apically into mesenteron. Mesenteron tubular, with a short mixed segment extending a little over the dilated portion of P1 (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FBE09387798703F4" box="[1103,1260,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Figs 15d, 15e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FB57938778E403F7" box="[1272,1423,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,189,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1337]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 17. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes tellustris. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e and f, mixed segment in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571711/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">17d, 17e, 17f</figureCitation>
). Two pairs of Malpighian tubules attached at mesenteron-proctodeum junction (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FBA293A379070388" box="[1037,1132,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Fig. 15e</figureCitation>
). P1 diagonal to body axis, enlarged and fusiform (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FE3693CF7C9703AC" box="[409,508,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Figs 15c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FDA993CF7F5903AC" box="[518,562,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,189,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1337]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 17. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes tellustris. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e and f, mixed segment in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571711/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">17c</figureCitation>
); distal end of P1 narrowed, forming short neck with P2 (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FB0793CF786703AC" box="[1192,1292,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Figs 15b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FAB993CF782A03AC" box="[1302,1345,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,189,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1337]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 17. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes tellustris. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e and f, mixed segment in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571711/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">17c</figureCitation>
), before attachment to P3 on left side of body. Enteric valve (P2) composed of three nearly equal conical ridges, covered with curved spines (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FEEC90377CCD0067" box="[323,422,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1309,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-259@12.[151,1435,1309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 14. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, gizzard; b, enteric valve." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571701/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
), [
<bibRefCitation id="EF83B4DAFFBD5721FE6D90377FF40064" author="Constantino, R." box="[450,671,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457" pagination="3 - 9" refId="ref8255" refString="Constantino, R. (1990) Two new species of termites (Insecta, Isoptera) from western Brazilian Amazonia. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, Serie Zoologia, 6 (1), 3 - 9." type="journal article" year="1990">Constantino (1990)</bibRefCitation>
fig. 12)]. Dorsal torsion well developed. Third proctodeal segment joined P4 by an 
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBD5721FEE290537CC80038" box="[333,419,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">isthmus</emphasis>
is inserted subapically (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FD1E90537E7E0038" box="[689,789,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Figs 15a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBD5721FC8E90537E270038" box="[801,844,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,189,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1337]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 17. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes tellustris. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e and f, mixed segment in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571711/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">17a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6D99A3FFBD5721FF3896F9796D075C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571697" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6571697" box="[151,1030,1261,1285]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571697/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457" startId="12.[151,250,1261,1285]" targetBox="[151,1435,633,1237]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBD5721FF3896F9796D075C" blockId="12.[151,1030,1261,1285]" box="[151,1030,1261,1285]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBD5721FF3896F97C4B075C" bold="true" box="[151,288,1261,1285]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">FIGURE 13.</emphasis>
Soldier of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBD5721FE3E96F97FFB075C" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[401,656,1261,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBD5721FE3E96F97FFB075C" box="[401,656,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Bandeiratermes silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF6D99A3FFBD5721FF3895A67EB30593" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571701" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6571701" box="[151,984,1970,1995]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571701/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="457" startId="12.[151,250,1970,1994]" targetBox="[151,1435,1309,1945]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBD5721FF3895A67EB30593" blockId="12.[151,984,1970,1995]" box="[151,984,1970,1995]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBD5721FF3895A67C4B0593" bold="true" box="[151,288,1970,1994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">FIGURE 14.</emphasis>
Worker gut of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBD5721FE1595A67FD20593" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[442,697,1970,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBD5721FE1595A67FD20593" box="[442,697,1970,1994]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="457">Bandeiratermes silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. a, gizzard; b, enteric valve.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBC5720FF68928278F80064" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FF6892827E7602E9" bold="true" box="[199,797,150,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">
Comparisons with other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FDDC92827E7602E9" authorityName="Engel &amp; Krishna" authorityYear="2004" box="[627,797,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Syntermitinae">Syntermitinae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Considering the diagnostic characters of the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FF3892AF7C5F028C" authorityName="Engel &amp; Krishna" authorityYear="2004" box="[151,308,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Syntermitinae">Syntermitinae</taxonomicName>
summarized above (
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FDB392AF7FFB028D" box="[540,656,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">vide supra</emphasis>
comparison with 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FCF892AF7EB8028D" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" box="[855,979,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Biratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FCF892AF7EB8028D" box="[855,979,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Biratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), it is most critical to compare 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FA8492AF7D8902A1" authority="Rocha &amp; Cancello, 2022" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FA8492AF7D8902A1" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Bandeiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FF4792CB7C5C02A0" bold="true" box="[232,311,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FF4792CB7C5C02A0" box="[232,311,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FEDA92CB7F7F02A0" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[373,532,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Embiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FEDA92CB7F7F02A0" box="[373,532,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Embiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FDB592CB7F5502A0" box="[538,574,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FDDB92CB7FB502A0" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[628,734,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Ibitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FDDB92CB7FB502A0" box="[628,734,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Ibitermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FD4B92CB7E6302A0" box="[740,776,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The soldiers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FC1392CB793002A0" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[956,1115,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Embiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FC1392CB793002A0" box="[956,1115,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Embiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FBCE92CB79EE02A0" box="[1121,1157,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have piercing mandibles with marginal teeth at the proximal third of the mandible length, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FC2D9317795E0344" authority="Rocha &amp; Cancello, 2022" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" box="[898,1077,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FC2D9317795E0344" box="[898,1077,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Bandeiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FB94931779E20344" bold="true" box="[1083,1161,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FB94931779E20344" box="[1083,1161,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the mandibles are blunter and the marginal teeth are reduced, located at the base of the mandibles (
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FC70933379120318" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[991,1145,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FC70933379670319" box="[991,1036,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Ban</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FBB6933379120318" box="[1049,1145,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBC5720FB289333798F0318" box="[1159,1252,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1261,1285]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,633,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-241@12.[151,1435,633,1237]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 13. Soldier of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571697/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FAC793337D92033C" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tellustris">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FAC793337D92033C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Ban. tellustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBC5720FEA7935F7C03033F" box="[264,360,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1112,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 16. Soldier of Bandeiratermes tellustris (Ibitermes tellustris paratype). a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571709/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Fig. 16a</figureCitation>
). The soldiers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FD82935F7FFC033C" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[557,663,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Ibitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FD82935F7FFC033C" box="[557,663,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Ibitermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FD31935F7FA9033C" box="[670,706,331,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have a markedly inflated postclypeus (absent in the new genus). The worker gut is well distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FD81937B7FA603D0" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[558,717,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Embiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FD81937B7FA603D0" box="[558,717,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Embiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FD7C937B7F9C03D0" box="[723,759,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the position and shape of the enteric valve segment, short and broad, at the middle of the abdomen length in 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FD7D93877E1A03F4" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[722,881,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Embiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FD7D93877E1A03F4" box="[722,881,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Embiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FCD793877EF703F4" box="[888,924,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBC5720FC0393877E9403F4" box="[940,1023,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,789,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-324@4.[151,1436,777,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Worker gut of Embiratermes festivellus. a, dorsal; b, left (arrow: P2 position); c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of mixed segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571679/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
, arrow), and with a long neck and at the end of the abdomen length in 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FDA493A37FD50388" authorityName="Rocha &amp; Cancello" authorityYear="2022" box="[523,702,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Bandeiratermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FDA493A37FD50388" box="[523,702,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Bandeiratermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBC5720FD7C93A37E530388" box="[723,824,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Figs 15b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBC5720FCEC93A37E1B038B" box="[835,880,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,189,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1337]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 17. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes tellustris. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e and f, mixed segment in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571711/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">17b</figureCitation>
). The worker gut of 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBC5720FBFC93A379D60388" authorityName="Fontes" authorityYear="1985" box="[1107,1213,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Ibitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBC5720FBFC93A379D60388" box="[1107,1213,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Ibitermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A255A842FFBC5720FB6C93A3798C0388" box="[1219,1255,439,465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have a long and twisted mesenteric tongue (short and rounded in 
